.TH "TD\-COMPLETIONS" "1" "2026" "TARDIS Manual"
.SH NAME
td\-completions \- generate shell completion scripts for td
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]td completions\f[R] \f[I]SHELL\f[R]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\f[B]td completions\f[R] generates shell completion scripts for the
specified shell and writes them to stdout.
Redirect the output to the appropriate file for your shell to enable tab
completions for all \f[B]td\f[R] commands, subcommands, and options.
.SH SHELLS
The following shells are supported:
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]bash\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]zsh\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]fish\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]elvish\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]powershell\f[R]
.SH EXAMPLES
Generate and install Bash completions:
.IP
.EX
td completions bash > \[ti]/.local/share/bash\-completion/completions/td
.EE
.PP
Generate and install Zsh completions:
.IP
.EX
td completions zsh > \[dq]${fpath[1]}/_td\[dq]
.EE
.PP
Generate and install Fish completions:
.IP
.EX
td completions fish > \[ti]/.config/fish/completions/td.fish
.EE
.PP
Generate Elvish completions:
.IP
.EX
td completions elvish > \[ti]/.config/elvish/lib/td.elv
.EE
.PP
Generate PowerShell completions:
.IP
.EX
td completions powershell > td.ps1
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
